title: Fix currency filter

title: fix(docs): use window.eval instead of window.execScript on IE
body:
IE doesn't have window.eval which our docs use. Instead there is
execScript, which however throws an exception when an empty string is
passed in, so I created a workaround with a workaround.

title: fix(markup): Make special attrs such as ng:href work even without binding
body:
fix(markup): Make special attrs such as ng:href work even without binding

their values do not contain bindings. And this commit is to fix that

feat($route): add ignoreHashSearch route param to avoid reloads
body:
In order to avoid unnecesary route reloads when just hashSearch part
of the url changes, it is now possible to add ignoreHashSearch:true
param to the route declaration.

title: doc(sample): Add javascript sandbox integration (jsFiddle)
body:
Change doc-widget.js to:

  - By default, render "edit in jsFiddle" button which posts live sample code to jsFiddle.

  - Handle new (and optional), <doc:sandbox/> tag in ngdocs which overrides default jsFiddle behvaior.
    If new xml tag has content, then extract and render new content.
    Do not render the xml tag(s).

  - Update stylesheet to make new "edit in jsFiddle" button consistent with angular documentation.
